  "slug": "whose-voice-calls-my-pleasure-selfish-journal",
  "title": "Whose Voice Calls My Pleasure Selfish?",
  "subtitle": "A journal practice for tracing where the pleasure guilt came from",
  "excerpt": "A journal practice for examining the source of pleasure guilt: the voice that arrives when you enjoy something and tells you it is selfish, unearned, or inappropriate. Traces where that voice came from and what it is still protecting.",
  "type": "PRACTICE",
  "sourceNotes": "Written for homemade.education.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A journal practice for tracing pleasure guilt to its source. Pleasure guilt is not innate. It was installed somewhere. This practice looks for where.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "New to journal prompts? Read ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "journal prompts as practice",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "/mindset/journal-prompts-as-practice"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": " first.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The practice",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Warm-up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Think of a recent moment when you felt guilty for enjoying something. What were you doing, and what did the guilt say?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write the specific pleasure and the specific guilt message. Not the general version. The exact thought that arrived.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Closer in",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whose voice does the guilty thought sound like?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "It will sound like someone. A parent, a teacher, a religious figure, a cultural rule absorbed from somewhere. Write whose voice it is, or whose it most resembles.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "What were you taught, explicitly or implicitly, about pleasure when you were growing up?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Not what you were told. What the rules were in practice. What happened when someone in your household rested without earning it. What the attitude to enjoyment was.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 4
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Is the voice telling you something that is still true for you now, or is it a rule from a context that no longer applies?",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Write what you actually think. Not what the voice says. What you, as an adult with your own life, believe about whether pleasure needs to be earned.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Where this practice comes from",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
